headlines.description: — Joel Embiid had 33 points and 14 rebounds, and his two free throws with 7.2 seconds left helped the Philadelphia 76ers seal a 114-110 victory over the Detroit Pistons on Saturday night.
headlines.shortLinkText: Embiid hits late free throws, 76ers beat Pistons 114-110

headlines.description: — Kevin Durant scored 31 points, Kyrie Irving took over late and had 28 and the Brooklyn Nets overcame Bam Adebayo's career-high 41 points to beat the Miami Heat 128-124 on Saturday night.
headlines.shortLinkText: Durant, Irving help Nets hold off Adebayo, Heat 128-124

events.name: New Orleans Pelicans at Minnesota Timberwolves

headlines.description: — Naz Reid scored 20 points to lead a balanced offensive effort and the Minnesota Timberwolves beat the New Orleans Pelicans 120-110 on Saturday night.
headlines.shortLinkText: Balanced attack leads Timberwolves past Pelicans 120-110

events.name: Golden State Warriors at Utah Jazz

headlines.description: — Donovan Mitchell had 23 points, seven rebounds and six assists as the Utah Jazz routed the Golden State Warriors 127-108 on Saturday night for their eighth straight victory.
headlines.shortLinkText: Jazz rout Warriors for 8th straight; Curry now 2nd in 3s

events.name: Los Angeles Lakers at Chicago Bulls

headlines.description: — Anthony Davis scored a season-high 37 points against his hometown team, LeBron James added 17 points and 11 rebounds and the Los Angeles Lakers beat the Chicago Bulls 101-90 on Saturday.
headlines.shortLinkText: Davis scores season-high 37 as Lakers beat Bulls 101-90

headlines.description: — Eric Gordon scored a season-high 33 points, DeMarcus Cousins had his best game for Houston with 28 points and 17 rebounds and the Rockets beat the Dallas Mavericks 133-108 on Saturday night.
headlines.shortLinkText: Gordon, Cousins help Rockets cruise past Mavericks, 133-108

headlines.description: — Nikola Jokic had 29 points and 22 rebounds, Jamal Murray hit a difficult 3-pointer to force overtime and the Denver Nuggets outlasted the Phoenix Suns 120-112 in two overtimes Saturday night.
headlines.shortLinkText: Jokic, Murray push Nuggets to 120-112 win over Suns in 2 OTs
